ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The class provided the basic tools to understand Randomized Algorithms. It was taught as a theoretical class. It did provide a few algorithms but did not give a data-bank. However, tools provided should be more then sufficient to study interdependently.
I would recommend this course to other students, and I would emphasize the heavy use of probability.
I am a fellow student. I will recommend it.
Yes, definitely take this course, especially if Jim is teaching it!

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It is very deep. I think it will help me to build a strong math background for my research.
